1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with coding and correlation between outputs of distributed codes, which are key topics in information theory. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper involves the study of binary block-codes and their dependency spectrums, which can be seen as a type of data structure. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may be relevant to the study of communication networks and their performance in multi-terminal settings. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve analyzing the computational complexity of the coding schemes considered. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may be relevant to the study of secure communication and the potential vulnerabilities of certain coding schemes.
